## Step 6
Using the fact that $P(I) = P(I \cap H) + P(I \cap N) + P(I \cap L)$, we can find $P(I \cap L)$. So, $P(I \cap L) = P(I) - P(I \cap H) - P(I \cap N) = 17\% - 5.95\% - 7.15\% = 3.9\%$.

## Step 7
Now, we need to find $P(L)$ and then $P(R \cap L)$. We know $P(L) = 19\%$. To find $P(R \cap L)$, we first find $P(R|L)$. Since $P(I|L) + P(R|L) = 1$, we need to calculate $P(I|L)$.

