The probability that there are no matches in $n$ trials can be calculated using the probability of no match on each trial. Assuming independence, this probability is $\left(1 - \frac{1}{n}\right)^n$.

## Step 4
The probability of at least one match is $1$ minus the probability of no matches. So, the probability of at least one match is $1 - \left(1 - \frac{1}{n}\right)^n$.

