## Step 5
Applying Chebyshev's inequality to $Y/n$, we have $P(|Y/n - 0.25| < 0.05) \geq 1 - \frac{0.1875/n}{(0.05)^2}$.

## Step 6
Substituting $n = 500$ into the inequality gives $P(|Y/n - 0.25| < 0.05) \geq 1 - \frac{0.1875/500}{(0.05)^2} = 1 - \frac{0.000375}{0.0025}$.

## Step 7
